      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 105,
      "message": "No. I think keeping the drawing code it in one place enables the reader to quickly follow through the flow instead of jumping through (presumably) three new classes. I will change method names to make them more descriptive though. In this case converting switch to a bunch of classes is not worth \"100% Object-Oriented Design Badge\".",
